# 🤖 AI Security Fundamentals

## 🎯 Objective
Develop practical skills to identify, analyze, and mitigate security risks in Large Language Models (LLMs), AI agents, Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) systems, and AI supply chains using defense-in-depth principles.

---

## 🛠 Tools & Technologies Used
- Large Language Models (LLMs)
- Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG)
- Vector Databases
- Prompt Engineering
- SafeTensors
- Pickle
- GGUF
- Fickling
- ModelScan
- SBOM (CycloneDX / SPDX)
- OWASP Top 10 for LLM Applications
- AI Threat Modeling

---

## 🔍 Activities Performed

### 🛡 Prompt Injection & Jailbreak Analysis
- Analyzed direct and indirect prompt injection attacks.
- Performed prompt jailbreak testing using role-play, multi-turn, and context manipulation techniques.
- Evaluated prompt hardening strategies and system prompt security.
- Studied AI guardrails, input validation, and output filtering techniques.

### 🤖 LLM Security
- Explored LLM attack surfaces and trust boundaries.
- Analyzed sensitive information disclosure risks in AI applications.
- Studied improper output handling and secure AI deployment practices.
- Applied defense-in-depth principles for AI systems.

### 📚 RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) Security
- Analyzed RAG architecture and retrieval workflows.
- Investigated vector database security and embedding-based retrieval.
- Studied retrieval abuse, context manipulation, and indirect prompt injection.
- Evaluated tenant isolation, metadata filtering, namespace segmentation, and retrieval access control.
- Investigated ingestion pipeline security and document validation.

### 🧬 AI Supply Chain Security
- Analyzed AI model supply chain attack vectors.
- Investigated malicious model serialization using Pickle.
- Compared Pickle, SafeTensors, Keras (.h5), and GGUF model formats.
- Studied model provenance, integrity verification, and secure model acquisition.
- Investigated dependency confusion, typosquatting, and model repository attacks.

### 🧪 AI Model Security Analysis
- Identified serialization-based attacks using Pickle (__reduce__ exploitation).
- Investigated architecture-level attacks such as malicious Keras Lambda layers.
- Performed static security analysis using Fickling and ModelScan.
- Evaluated model integrity through checksums and security scanning.

### ☣️ AI Data & Model Poisoning
- Studied training data poisoning attacks.
- Investigated embedding poisoning and corpus poisoning.
- Analyzed ingestion pipeline attacks and retrieval manipulation.
- Evaluated behavioral drift caused by poisoned datasets.

### 🔒 AI Defensive Security
- Implemented layered security controls for AI systems.
- Applied prompt hardening and structured prompt templates.
- Evaluated AI guardrails for input and output validation.
- Studied secure logging, monitoring, and anomaly detection.
- Applied least privilege and zero-trust principles to AI deployments.

